@node "Bugs" " Bugs         "
Known Bugs

-On 15/16/24 Bit (CybergraphX-) Screens the right and the lower
 edge of the snowflakes are cut off.

 This seems to be a bug in CybergraphX (I got 2.08 at this time).
 Or is it my fault (please tell me, if you know) ?

-On 15/16/24 Bit (CybergraphX-) Screens the V39 Version isn't working.

 This seems also to be a CybergraphX-Bug.

-"The V40 Version is slooow on my EGS-Screens"

 That's a problem of the EGS-Emulation (I got 7.2), which does
 not emulate the WriteChunkyPixels()-function. Use the V39
 Version!

-"Whuaahh, my monitor burnt in"

 You checked '@{"Keep Snow" link "Options" 0}'. If you know that you'll blank for
 a long time with BTDSnow, turn 'Keep snow' off! @{"->Disclaimer" link "Disclaimer" 0}
@endnode

